{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, we will also investigate the evolution of the average population opinionm w (t) = 1 ∑ j∈{a,u,i} ρ j (t) ∫ R×I wf (t, A, w)dAdw(9)and of the average level of activity of the populationm A (t) = 1 ∑ j∈{a,u,i} ρ j (t) ∫ R×I Af (t, A, w)dAdw.",
    "(10)Finally, we shall denote with f ℓ = f ℓ (z) the (static) opinion distribution of the leaders, satisfying ∫ I f ℓ (z)dz = 1, and with µ ℓ = ∫ I zf ℓ (z)dz their constant average opinion.",
    "By classical methods of kinetic theory [28] and resorting to the derivation of the classical linear Boltzmann equation for elastic rarefied gases [8], one can show that the time variation of the distribution function f (t, A, w) depends on a sequence of elementary binary interactions of type ( 2) and (3).",
    "In our case, for all smooth functions φ = φ(A, w) (the observable quantities), the following linear integro-differential equation holds:d dt ∫ R×I φ(A, w)f (t, A, w)dAdw = ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ⟨φ(A ′, w ′) -φ(A, w)⟩ f (t, A, w)f (t, B, v)dAdBdwdv + ∫ R×I 2 ⟨φ(A ′, w ′) -φ(A, w)⟩ f (t, A, w)f ℓ (z)dAdwdz,(11)where the first term represents the interactions agent-agent (2), while the second one accounts for the interactions agent-leaders (3).",
    "The choice φ ≡ 1 in (11) leads to the conservation of mass, i.e., the total number of agents inside the population does not change."
  ]
}